WEBVTT

00:00.339 --> 00:03.601
Let's work on forming the /æ/ sound.

00:04.937 --> 00:09.687
The tip of your tongue is relaxed and touching behind the lower front teeth.

00:10.509 --> 00:12.967
Keep your lips relaxed.

00:14.175 --> 00:16.323
Drop your jaw down low.

00:16.712 --> 00:20.315
Here's /æ/ in the beginning of some words.

00:21.619 --> 00:26.461
Apple, After, Ask.

00:27.263 --> 00:29.221
And here it is in the middle.

00:30.183 --> 00:34.962
Flap, Passed, Happy.

00:36.447 --> 00:41.165
The /æ/ never appears at the end of words in English.

00:42.694 --> 00:46.823
Listen to these pairs of words to hear the contrasting sounds.

00:47.777 --> 00:50.421
Dancer, Denser.

00:51.869 --> 00:54.822
Pat, Pet.

00:55.993 --> 00:58.699
Sand, Send.

00:59.757 --> 01:02.525
Man, Men.

01:04.636 --> 01:09.106
Here are some sentences that use the /æ/ sound.

01:11.141 --> 01:15.549
Sandy was happy to ask for bananas and apples.

01:17.268 --> 01:20.376
Pat sat in the sandy landrover.

01:21.426 --> 01:22.255
Good luck!

